The paper deals with speaker verification, which is a subfield of speech processing and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.SD (Sound) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely categories. The use of deep learning approaches and convolutional neural networks suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper deals with signal processing and feature extraction, which could fall under cs.SI (Signal Processing).
